      <font size=3 color="008000"><b>Color / Site Info Section - Site Color Customization:</b></font><br><br>
      This section of the Visual Auction Server Administrator allows you to define the colors
      shown on your site for links, backgrounds, and listings.  With stylesheet
      code, you can also specify the font face and attributes used for the text on your
      site.
      <br><br>
      <b>Link</b> - Specifies the text color used for normal, unvisited hypertext <a href="#">links</a>.<br><br>
      <b>Visited Link</b> - Specifies the text color used for hypertext visited links.<br><br>
      <b>Active Link</b> - Specifies the text color used for active (when the mouse button is pressed down over the link) hypertext links.<br><br>
      <b>Page Text</b> - Specifies the text color used all text on the site.  This can be overridden by CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) code.<br><br>
      <b>Page Background</b> - Specifies the background color used on all pages, visible behind the text and images.<br><br>
      <b>Heading</b>- Specifies the color in the heading box on the entire site unless changed in the category area.<br><br>
      <b>Heading Font Color</b>- Specifies the color of the text in the heading box on the entire site again unless change in the category area.<br><br>
      <b>Heading Font</b>- This determines the text style in the heading boxes.<br><br> 
      <b>Ending Auction</b> - Specifies the text color to show when an auction is close to ending.<br><br>
     </font>
