     <font size=2>      
      <b>Listing Background</b> - Specifies the background color to show alternate listing rows in when long lists of items are displayed on one screen.  Set this to the same color as the background to turn the alternating bars off.<br><br>
      <b>Page CSS Code</b> - Put any CSS code in this box, and it will take effect for all pages site-wide.  This allows you to set the font size, color, and style for all text on the site.  Refer to a CSS reference manual for details.<br><br>
      <b>Rotating Banner Script</b>- This area will allow you to display up to 9 banners on a rotating basis throughout your site located below the menu bar.<br><br>
      <b>Modify VA Menu Bar</b>- From this area you can add or delete links from your menu bar without having to edit any of the script files.<br><br>
      <b>News and Announcements</b> - This area you use to post any news you have or events you have planned in the future. You can also use html in this area.<br><br>
      <b>Predefined Color Table</b> - These are how the predefined colors in the drop-down menus actually look.  For colors other than these, select "Custom Color" from any of the drop-down boxes and type in its 6-digit RGB hexadecimal value.  Refer to an HTML reference manual for more information on composing custom colors.<br><br>
